            <xs:documentation source="Definition" xml:lang="EN">The FedNow Message Identification is a reference assigned by the sender of the message. It is composed of the Calendar Date (8 numeric characters, CCYYMMDD), the sender's FedNow Connection Party Identification (9 alphanumeric characters) and a reference assigned by the sender (up to 18 alphanumeric characters).</xs:documentation>
